{% if layout_signals_json %}
COMPUTED LAYOUT SIGNALS (extracted from rendered page via Playwright):
Use these to evaluate benefit_hierarchy, dtc_benchmark/scannability, and dtc_benchmark/mobile_structure.
Key fields:
- benefit_section.display / columns: whether benefits use grid/flex and how many columns
- benefit_section.icon_paired_with_heading: true = 3-part layout detected
- benefit_section.highlight_count: number of distinct benefit highlights
- benefit_section.avg_paragraph_chars: long = wall of text, short = scannable
- nutrition.is_html_table / position_percent_down_page: table present and where on the page
- nutrition.in_popup_or_modal: true = nutritional information is behind a popup/modal button — this is a PASS for semantic_grouping_of_details (spec data is fully separated from persuasive content)
- gallery.nav_type: "thumbnails" or "dots"
- main_layout.columns: 1 = mobile-friendly single column
- review_trust_signals.star_filter_controls_found: interactive star-rating filter controls exist in the DOM
- review_trust_signals.rating_breakdown_bars_found: 1★–5★ percentage breakdown bars present
- review_trust_signals.verified_badge_found / verified_badge_text_samples: verified buyer badges detected and their text
- review_trust_signals.low_star_reviews_visible: 1-star or 2-star review content is visible on the page (not suppressed)
- review_trust_signals.review_card_count: number of individual review cards rendered in the DOM
- review_trust_signals.rating_widget_position: "atf_or_near" or "below_fold" (aggregate star rating widget location)
- catalog_differentiation.comparison_table_found: a multi-column product comparison table exists in the DOM
- catalog_differentiation.variant_buttons_found / variant_names_found: button-style variant selectors and their labels
- catalog_differentiation.variant_dropdowns_found: dropdown selectors (lower UX quality than buttons)
- catalog_differentiation.compare_language_detected: "vs", "compare", "difference between" language present
- catalog_differentiation.tab_labels: visible tab labels (may indicate hidden comparison content)

For trust_signals/authenticity_and_negative_review_visibility:
- pass: verified_badge_found=true AND (star_filter_controls_found=true OR rating_breakdown_bars_found=true) AND low_star_reviews_visible=true
- partial: verified badges OR filter controls present but not both, OR low_star_reviews_visible=false (negative reviews may be suppressed)
- fail: none of the above signals present

For trust_signals/prominent_aggregate_ratings: use rating_widget_position to confirm ATF placement — "atf_or_near" confirms the rating is above or near the fold; "below_fold" or "not_found" downgrades the score.

For product_positioning/internal_catalog_differentiation: if catalog_differentiation.comparison_table_found is true, score as pass. If variant_buttons_found but no comparison table, score as partial. If neither, score as fail (or N/A if variant_names_found is empty and the product appears to be single-SKU).
