ATF SCREENSHOT PROVIDED: A real mobile screenshot (390×844px, no scroll) is attached.

CRITICAL RULES FOR ATF SCORING:
- Score headline_clarity and dtc_benchmark/above_fold_completeness ONLY from what is physically visible in this screenshot.
- A field existing in the structured data does NOT mean it is visible ATF. The price may be in the data but below the fold.
- For each headline_clarity element check, look at the screenshot first. If you cannot see it in the screenshot, it is NOT present ATF.

ATF CITATION FORMAT — this is mandatory:
  For every element check in headline_clarity, your cited fact MUST describe what you
  see in the screenshot, not what is in the structured data.
  CORRECT: "fail — no pricing text visible in screenshot ATF"
  CORRECT: "pass — cost-per-serving visible in screenshot below product title"
  WRONG:   "pass — price '£29.99' present in structured data" ← flagged as false positive
  WRONG:   "Cost-per-serving is missing, forcing users to calculate the value of the £50 product" ← never quote specific prices

PRICE RULE — NON-NEGOTIABLE:
  Never quote or reference any specific price value (e.g. £50, £29.99, £1.67/serving) in any
  element check, score rationale, or recommendation. Only state whether cost-per-serving
  is visible or not visible. The specific price is irrelevant to the audit findings.

SPECIFIC ATF CHECKS:
- price_visibility: FAIL unless a cost-per-serving figure is legible in the screenshot.
  Do not quote the price value. State only "cost-per-serving visible" or "cost-per-serving missing".
  The structured.price field WILL mislead you — ignore it for this check entirely.
- prominent_cta: FAIL unless the Add to Basket / Buy Now button is physically visible in
  the screenshot. cta_buttons in structured data does NOT confirm ATF placement.
- outcome_sub_headline: FAIL unless a benefit-led sentence is visible below the H1 in
  the screenshot. Product name or category label does not count.
- per_serving_cost: FAIL unless a cost-per-serving figure is legible in the screenshot.
  Do not infer it from price + serving count in structured data.
